  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indigenous and Rural Families in Beni Diversify Their Production Systems to Achieve Food Security</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The municipalities of Baures, San Andr&#xE9;s and San Javier are in the Department of Beni, on the floodplain of the Mamor&#xE9; River Basin, with a multi-ethnic population (local indigenous and mixed-ancestry people, and highlands and valley indigenous people (Quechua and Aymara). In the last 6 years, the region has experienced continual cycles of floods, droughts and forest fires, devastating the wildlife and directly affecting the livelihoods of indigenous and rural families, undermining their food security system, and causing poverty and hunger. In this context, the project &#x201C;will contribute to improving food production and organizational leadership for 126 indigenous and rural families in 9 communities of three municipalities in the department of Beni&#x201D;.</narrative>
  </description>
